<p>The success of Wilds helped lift Capcom to its <a href="https://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/news/html/e250513b.html" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">eighth straight year of profit and 10th consecutive year of more than 10% operating income growth. </a></p><p>The game sold <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/monster-hunter-wilds-becomes-capcoms-fastest-selling-game-in-just-3-days/1100-6529838/" data-ref-id="1100-6529838">more than 8 million copies over its first three days, becoming Capcom's fastest-selling game ever.</a> It went on to <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/monster-hunter-wilds-hits-a-massive-milestone-free-item-pack-coming-to-celebrate/1100-6530490/" data-ref-id="1100-6530490">sell 10 million copies in its first month.</a></p><p>It still has work to do to catch Monster Hunter World, though, which has sold 21 million+ copies and is <a href="https://www.capcom.co.jp/ir/english/business/million.html" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Capcom's best-selling game of all time globally.</a></p><p>Overall, the Monster Hunter franchise is the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/capcoms-best-selling-game-franchises-of-all-time-and-whats-next-for-each/2900-6294/">second-best-selling Capcom franchise of all time</a>, with Resident Evil still holding the top spot.</p><p>"There are a few missteps along the way--of both an artistic and technical variety--but Wilds is another excellent entry in Capcom's beloved series," Richard Wakeling wrote in GameSpot's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/monster-hunter-wilds-review-new-frontier/1900-6418338/">Monster Hunter Wilds review</a>. If you've just gotten started on the game, you can also check out GameSpot's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/monster-hunter-wilds-guides-hub/1100-6529740/">Monster Hunter Wilds guides hub</a> for several helpful features and <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/psa-monsters-can-rudely-crash-your-bb